$ Examples for Visual Basic for Application accessing the Windows API: SetWindowsPos

This example starts notepad with → development/languages/VBA/Win-API/examples/ShellExecute[`ShellExecute`] and finds its handle with
`FindWindow` and then places the notepad window to the topmost position using the `SetWindowPos` WinAPI call.

This example needs the VBA declarations of the Windows API which can be found
→ development/languages/VBA/Win-API[here].

gh|WinAPI-4-VBA|/examples/SetWindowPos/HWND_TOPMOST.bas||

sa:

  → development/languages/VBA/Win-API/examples[Other examples]
